---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Licensing"
  description="Licensing terms for the QIF framework, TARA threat atlas, NSP protocol, and related materials."
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Licensing' }]}
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-4">Licensing</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed mb-12">
      Qinnovate publishes open standards for BCI security. Different assets carry different licenses to balance adoption with protection.
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-8">

      <!-- Framework Specifications -->
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="text-2xl">&#x1f4d0;</div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-1">Framework Specifications</h2>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-accent-primary)] font-medium mb-3">CC BY-SA 4.0</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed mb-3">
              The QIF hourglass architecture, NSP protocol specification, and TARA schema definitions are licensed under
              <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-[var(--color-accent-primary)] hover:underline">Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0</a>.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed">
              You may use, adapt, and build upon these specifications — including implementing them in your own BCI systems — provided you give attribution and share any modifications under the same terms.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">
              Covers: QIF layer model, NSP validation layers, TARA four-projection schema, QNIS scoring methodology, hourglass band definitions
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- QTARA Registry Data -->
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="text-2xl">&#x1f6e1;</div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-1">QTARA Registry Data</h2>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-accent-secondary)] font-medium mb-3">CC BY-NC-SA 4.0</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed mb-3">
              The TARA threat registry entries, technique descriptions, QNIS scores, and therapeutic mappings are licensed under
              <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-[var(--color-accent-secondary)] hover:underline">Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0</a>.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed">
              Researchers may use, extend, and publish extensions of the registry for non-commercial purposes. Commercial use — including embedding registry data in commercial products or services — requires a separate license from Qinnovate.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">
              Covers: All 71 TARA technique entries, severity scores, therapeutic/diagnostic/governance projections, attack chain mappings
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Blog Posts -->
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="text-2xl">&#x1f4dd;</div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-1">Blog Posts</h2>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-accent-tertiary)] font-medium mb-3">CC BY 4.0</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed mb-3">
              All blog posts and editorial content are licensed under
              <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-[var(--color-accent-tertiary)] hover:underline">Creative Commons Attribution 4.0</a>.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed">
              Share, quote, excerpt, translate, and republish freely — including commercially — with attribution to Qinnovate. The more this work spreads, the safer BCIs become.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">
              Covers: All blog posts, case studies, editorial content
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Whitepaper -->
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="text-2xl">&#x1f4dc;</div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-1">QIF Whitepaper</h2>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-accent-tertiary)] font-medium mb-3">CC BY-ND 4.0</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed mb-3">
              The QIF whitepaper is licensed under
              <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/4.0/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-[var(--color-accent-tertiary)] hover:underline">Creative Commons Attribution-NoDerivatives 4.0</a>.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed">
              Share, cite, and reference freely — including in commercial reports and publications — with attribution. The whitepaper must be shared in its original form to protect the integrity of the framework's core arguments.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">
              Covers: QIF whitepaper and formal technical publications
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Website Code -->
      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-6">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="text-2xl">&#x1f4bb;</div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-1">Website Code</h2>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)] font-medium mb-3">MIT License</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed">
              The website source code (Astro components, layouts, styling, build configuration) is available under the
              <a href="https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)] hover:underline">MIT License</a>.
              The data and content displayed by this code are covered by their respective licenses above.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Commercial Licensing -->
    <div class="mt-12 glass rounded-xl p-8 border border-[var(--color-accent-primary)]/20">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-4">Commercial Licensing</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
        BCI manufacturers, healthcare companies, and commercial entities seeking to implement QIF, embed TARA registry data, or deploy NSP in commercial products can contact us for commercial licensing terms.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Our goal is adoption, not gatekeeping. Commercial licenses exist to ensure the framework is implemented correctly and safely in devices that interface with human brains — not to restrict access.
      </p>
      <a
        href="mailto:kevin@qinnovate.com"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-[var(--color-accent-primary)]/10 text-[var(--color-accent-primary)] text-sm font-medium hover:bg-[var(--color-accent-primary)]/20 transition-colors"
      >
        Contact for commercial licensing
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- Summary Table -->
    <div class="mt-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-6">Summary</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">
              <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4 text-[var(--color-text-muted)] font-medium">Asset</th>
              <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4 text-[var(--color-text-muted)] font-medium">License</th>
              <th class="text-center py-3 pr-4 text-[var(--color-text-muted)] font-medium">Share</th>
              <th class="text-center py-3 pr-4 text-[var(--color-text-muted)] font-medium">Adapt</th>
              <th class="text-center py-3 text-[var(--color-text-muted)] font-medium">Commercial</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
            <tr class="border-b border-[var(--color-border)]/50">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Framework specs</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-[var(--color-accent-primary)]">CC BY-SA</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-center">Yes</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-center">Yes</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-center">Yes</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-[var(--color-border)]/50">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Threat registry</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-[var(--color-accent-secondary)]">CC BY-NC-SA</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-center">Yes</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-center">Yes</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-center">License required</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-[var(--color-border)]/50">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Blog posts</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-[var(--color-accent-tertiary)]">CC BY</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-center">Yes</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-center">Yes</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-center">Yes</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-[var(--color-border)]/50">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Whitepaper</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-[var(--color-accent-tertiary)]">CC BY-ND</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-center">Yes</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-center">No</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-center">Yes</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Website code</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">MIT</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-center">Yes</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-center">Yes</td>
              <td class="py-3 text-center">Yes</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-12 text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">
      All licenses require attribution to Qinnovate and Kevin Qi. For questions about licensing not covered here, contact kevin@qinnovate.com.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
